r"""
VaultWalker v0.5 — Universal, autonomous, silo-limited sub-agent for twice-daily (12h) re-read housekeeping.

Fully encapsulates distilled lessons from the 5 key X posts/threads (reviewed end-to-end):
- 2074255821211312609: Periodic active re-reads to catch dups + surface forgotten projects (~60d). Indexes + manifests as enablers (not naive full scans). Active maintenance to prevent landfill.
- 2074069045561717168 + 2071857253360054272: PKG architecture (user-centric entities/relations/context/action/update). 10 shifts: local MD substrate, atomic notes, MOCs, YAML metadata, query/resurface, link on entry, separate capture/processing.
- 2073191307175231795: Agentic OS — clean structured vaults enable dashboards/UI for automations as lifetime assets.
- 2072802530883752030: Self-evolving second brain (Hermes + Obsidian): periodic scans → extract/create reusable skills/workflows. Incremental + local models for scale.
- 2073071937979347129 + 2071860243911356416: Separation of concerns — one folder per concern/project (numbered), root INDEX.md as the "map" ("Where To Go" + canonicals + archive exclusion). Minimize depth. Agent reads INDEX first. "Smallest cage that works". Diagnostics on task time/wrong files.

Grand Vision: T0 silo population PRIMARY (hard-drives-first); T2 hygiene CONTINUOUS; Wisdom Keeper (Vault=how we work, K=what lived); high-signal; autonomous loops.

v0.5 iterations (robust, intuitive, thorough, future-proof):
- Persistent cross-run state (per-folder mtime + hash in manifests) → true incremental deep work.
- Staggered cycles (light: indexes + quick stale/dups; deep: full PKG/review/self-evo/LLM).
- Simulated agent diagnostics (estimated files opened, time saved via scaffolding, before/after impact).
- Structured human-verification proposals with diffs (never auto-apply destructive).
- Executable INDEX templates (sample agent prompts, "Read this map first", PKG/resurface guidance).
- Trend tracking (running metrics: % PKG coverage, avg alignment, resurfaced count, self-evo proposals, alignment trend).
- Full local Ollama integration (entities/relations, alignment, proposals) when local_first.
- Universal: config-driven (add future silos in data_silos.yaml; script auto-adapts, creates default VAULTWALKER.md if missing).
- Autonomous-ready: self-documenting logs, error resilience, always-produces reports/proposals/status, dry-run support.

Run: python "D:/HermesData/scripts/vaultwalker.py" [--dry-run] [--silos HermesData PhronesisVault ...]
12h cron (autonomous while traveling): see run_daily_vaultwalker.sh or Windows Task Scheduler instructions below.
Sub-agents strictly limited to one silo root. Local-first. Config-driven for any future silos.
"""

